1. The FileOutputStream class is meant to be used to read streams of raw bytes.
Ans: This is false

2. It is recommended the _______ class be used to read in streams of characters.
Ans: FileReader

3. Wrap FileWriters in a BufferedWriter class to improve memory management and
  use system resources more efficiently while maintaining the advantages of the FileWriter class.
Ans: This is true

4. What Scanner class method could you use to determine if there is another token in your input?
Ans: hasNext()
